headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 29 points, 18 rebounds and 16 assists, becoming only the second player in NBA history to reach those totals in a game, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Brooklyn Nets 144-139 in overtime on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 29 points, 18 rebounds and 16 assists to lead Nuggets past Nets 144-139 in OT

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 16 of his 35 points in the third quarter, Luka Doncic had a late surge to finish with 24 points, nine assists and eight rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks held off the <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks fend off Timberwolves 120-114 in West finals rematch behind Irving's 35 points

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 28 points and 11 rebounds, De'Aaron Fox added 19 points and the Sacramento Kings dominated the reeling Utah Jazz 113-96 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis scores 28 points as the Kings run past the punchless Jazz, 113-96

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored a season-best 28 points, Brandin Podziemski had 19 points and fueled a furious second-half comeback, and the Golden State Warriors rallied from down 20 early to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 124-106 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Missing starters Curry and Wiggins, Warriors use their depth to rally past the Pelicans 124-106
